GENERAL QUESTIONS

When will the event be held?

SunNUS 2019 will be held on Saturday, 15th June 2019.

What should I bring for the event?

You should bring a spare change of clothes, some money and identification (NRIC or matriculation card). For a detailed list, refer to your participant briefing!

What should I wear?

You should wear the SunNUS 2019 singlet provided. This allows our referees and volunteers to identify you! Refer to participant's brief for more information.

Is there a minimum age requirement?

The is no minimum age to participate and volunteer in SunNUS 2019 as of 15th June 2019.

How to get to Siloso Beach?

The beach is within walking distance from Beach station. Refer to your participants brief for specific directions.

What will happen if it rains?

SunNUS will proceed on despite light rain! In the event of thunderstorms, all activities will be halted and resumption of events will be strictly decided by the Organising Committee and Safety Officer. 

What if I do not bring my NRIC/matriculation card?

The committee will disqualify you from the activities. So, remind each other to bring it! 

WITHDRAWALS

Do I get a refund if I choose not to participate after registering?

No, any withdrawals are strictly non-refundable.

What if I am unable to participate in SunNUS and have already registered, how can I collect my goodie bag and event singlet?

Look out for the participant's brief. You may still collect the goodie bag and event singlet.

What if my team members are late?

As a volunteer for SunNUS 2019, you will get an exclusive volunteer singlet, goodie bag and lunch for the event day! Additionally, you will be awarded CIP hours if you stay for the entire event!

You may indicate your interest to volunteer on our MIC routes, TSS games or our Fringe games. More details can be found on the registration portal.
